lab 10
pg 602, # 17.3

(ArrayIndexOutBoundsException) Write a program that meets the following
requirements:
- create an array with one hundred randomly chosen integers.
- create a text field to enter an array index and another text field to
  display the array element at the specified index (See Figure 17.12).
- create a "Show Element" button to cause the array element to be dislayed. If
  the specified index is out of bounds, display the message "Out of Bound".
- also make sure to catch "NumberFormatException"

  Figure 17.12:
    The program displays the array element at the specified index or displays
    the message "Out of Bound" if the index is out of bounds.

  +---------------------------------------+
  | Exercise17_3: ShowError        _ O X  |
  |---------------------------------------|
  |                                       |
  | Array Index       [________________]  |
  |                                       |
  | Array Element     [  Out of Bound  ]  |
  |                                       |
  | ____________________________________  |
  | |                                  |  |
  | |          SHOW ELEMENT            |  |
  | |__________________________________|  |
